{"lemma":"شُرُدُ","slug":"شُرُدُ","root":"ش.ر.د","root_slug":"ش-ر-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ر-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شُرُدُ","root":"شرد","pos":"V","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22088","n22091"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%8F%D8%AF%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"fugitive; runaway; deserter; defector","examples":[{"text":"رَجُلٌ شَارِدٌ","english":"a fugitive man"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"straying; astray","examples":[{"text":"حَيَوَانٌ شَارِدٌ","english":"a stray animal"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"frightened; intimidated; helpless; at a loss","examples":[{"text":"كَانَ شَارِدًا","english":"he was frightened / at a loss"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"absent-minded; distracted","examples":[{"text":"شَارِدُ الْفِكْرِ","english":"absent-minded"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"uprooted; lacking stability; vagrant","examples":[{"text":"إِنْسَانٌ شَارِدٌ","english":"a rootless person"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"vagrant; tramp; vagabond","examples":[{"text":"يَعِيشُ كَشَارِدٍ","english":"he lives as a vagabond"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"irregularity; anomaly (especially in language)","examples":[{"text":"شَوَارِدُ اللُّغَةِ","english":"irregularities of the language"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From شَرَدَ (šarada, “to flee, run away, stray”), from the root ش ر د (š r d)."},"ipa":["/ʃaː.rid/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22088","headword_ar":"شَرَدَ","root":"$rd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uruwdN","text_ar":"شُرُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iraAdN","text_ar":"شِرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) or the latter is a simple subst., (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uraAdN","text_ar":"شُرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arodN","text_ar":"شَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) said of a camel, (S, A, L, Msb,) and of a horse or the like, (L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took fright,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shied, and fled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ran away at random;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became refractory, and went away at random,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ran away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broke loose, and went hither and thither by reason of his sprightliness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafara","text_ar":"نَفَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nad~a","text_ar":"نَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he fled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ran away;"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a camel &c. (Aboo-Bekr, TA.) The saying of the Prophet,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaA ya$orudu bika baEiyruka","text_ar":"اَمَا يَشْرُدُ بِكَ بَعِيرُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Does not thy camel take fright and run away with thee?"},{"kind":"text","text":"], addressed by him to Khowwát, who answered,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaA muno*u qay~adahu AlA_isolaAmu falaA","text_ar":"اَمَا مُنْذُ قَيَّدَهُ الاـِسْلَامُ فَلَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"As to the period since El-Islám shackled him, no"},{"kind":"text","text":"], mentioned in the A, points to a story related of Khowwát Ibn-Jubeyr, (TA,) that, being found by the Prophet sitting by some strange women, he endeavoured to excuse himself by saying that he had a camel which took fright and ran away, and he was seeking for something wherewith to shackle him: the Prophet used afterwards to taunt him by inquiring of him respecting the running-away of his camel: what Kr says, and J in the S [in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nHY","text_ar":"نحى"},{"kind":"text","text":"], is incorrect. (IAth, L.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arada Ean~iY fulaAnN","text_ar":"شَرَدَ عَنِّى فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one fled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aside"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apart"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a distance, from me;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafara","text_ar":"نَفَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) [Or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arada","text_ar":"شَرَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a man, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uruwdN","text_ar":"شُرُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He departed, driven away."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arada EalaY A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"شَرَدَ عَلَى ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He departed from obedience to God, and seceded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"separated himself from the community"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the faithful"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","Msb","K","A","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n22091","headword_ar":"شَرَدٌ","root":"$rd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAridN","text_ar":"شَارِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}